[size=4][b]What[/b][/size]

[size=3]Turns garden apple trees, berry bushes, and bee hives into passive producers that drop harvests for you to pick up, with an optional "realistic" mode that randomises drop timing and rewards manual harvesting.[/size]

[size=3][b]Base behaviour[/b][/size]
[list]
[*][size=3][b]Auto-drop for garden trees, bushes, and hives[/b] — your planted apple trees, berry bushes, and bee hives drop their harvest onto the ground when ready, so you can loot without clicking each one individually.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]World berry bushes (optional)[/b] — opt-in toggle. Turns the wild berry bushes around the map into auto-droppers too. Warning: if you don't regularly loot, the dropped items persist forever and hurt performance. Pair with [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/51]Auto-Loot Heavies[/url] or [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/62]Where's Ma' Storage[/url] for an auto-cleanup strategy.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Harvest-ready notifications[/b] — optional on-screen alert when a harvest becomes available.[/size]
[/list]

[size=3][b]Realistic harvest mode (optional)[/b][/size]
[list]
[*][size=3][b]Randomised drop timing[/b] — harvests arrive 2-15 seconds after becoming ready instead of landing the instant the bush/tree ripens.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Partial drops[/b] — if you leave it for the passive drop, you get between 2 and the crop's maximum (3 for bushes, 10 for trees, 1 for hives). The game drops less than the full max.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Manual harvesting gets the full amount[/b] — interacting directly always gives you the whole yield. Encourages you to tend the garden if you want maximum output.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Bee hives in realistic mode[/b] drop a maximum of 1 honey, 1 bee, and 1 wax passively. Manual harvest gives the full amount.[/size]
[/list]

[size=3][b]Other[/b][/size]
[list]
[*][size=3][b]Beekeeper buys excess[/b] — the beekeeper NPC now accepts surplus honey/bees/wax as sell items if you've over-produced.[/size]
[/list]

[size=3]No unlock required — the mod activates on any apple tree, berry bush, or bee hive the game considers "ready" to harvest, right from the first day you have a garden.[/size]

[size=4][b]Other mods of mine you might like[/b][/size]

[list]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/76]Where's Ma' Veggies[/url] — simultaneously harvest every plot of the same crop (Farmer perk required).[/size]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/58]The Seed Equalizer[/url] — stops garden seed counts from bleeding dry over time.[/size]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/62]Where's Ma' Storage[/url] — shared inventory, recommended if you enable wild-bush harvesting (auto-pools drops into stockpiles).[/size]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/70]Give Me Moar[/url] — multiplier on fruit/berry/honey drops.[/size]
[/list]

